21 // Liftoff Frames.
22 //
23 // slot Frame
24 // +--------------------+---------------------------
25 // n+4 | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
26 // n+3 | parameter n |
27 // ... | ... |
28 // 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
29 // 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
30 // 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
31 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
32 // 1 | return addr (ra) |
33 // 0 | previous frame (fp)|
34 // -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
35 // -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
36 // -2 | instance |
37 // -3 | feedback vector|
38 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
39 // -4 | slot 0 | ^
40 // -5 | slot 1 | |
41 // | | Frame slots
42 // | | |
43 // | | v
44 // | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
45 // -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
46 //
47 
48 inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
49 
50 inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
51  return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);
52 }
53 
54 template <typename T>
55 inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register addr,
56  Register offset, T offset_imm,
57  bool i64_offset = false, unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
58  if (offset != no_reg) {
59  if (!i64_offset) {
60  assm->Dext(kScratchReg, offset, 0, 32);
61  offset = kScratchReg;
62  }
63  if (shift_amount != 0) {
64  assm->Dlsa(kScratchReg, addr, offset, shift_amount);
65  } else {
66  assm->daddu(kScratchReg, offset, addr);
67  }
68  addr = kScratchReg;
69  }
70  if (is_int31(offset_imm)) {
71  int32_t offset_imm32 = static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm);
72  return MemOperand(addr, offset_imm32);
73  } else {
74  assm->li(kScratchReg2, Operand(offset_imm));
75  assm->daddu(kScratchReg, addr, kScratchReg2);
76  return MemOperand(kScratchReg, 0);
77  }
78 }
79 
80 inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, MemOperand src,
81  ValueKind kind) {
82  switch (kind) {
83  case kI16:
84  assm->Lh(dst.gp(), src);
85  break;
86  case kI32:
87  assm->Lw(dst.gp(), src);
88  break;
89  case kI64:
90  case kRef:
91  case kRefNull:
92  assm->Ld(dst.gp(), src);
93  break;
94  case kF32:
95  assm->Lwc1(dst.fp(), src);
96  break;
97  case kF64:
98  assm->Ldc1(dst.fp(), src);
99  break;
100  case kS128:
101  assm->ld_b(dst.fp().toW(), src);
102  break;
103  default:
104  UNREACHABLE();
105  }
106 }
107 
108 inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst, LiftoffRegister src,
109  ValueKind kind) {
110  switch (kind) {
111  case kI16:
112  assm->Ush(src.gp(), dst, t8);
113  break;
114  case kI32:
115  assm->Usw(src.gp(), dst);
116  break;
117  case kI64:
118  case kRefNull:
119  case kRef:
120  assm->Usd(src.gp(), dst);
121  break;
122  case kF32:
123  assm->Uswc1(src.fp(), dst, t8);
124  break;
125  case kF64:
126  assm->Usdc1(src.fp(), dst, t8);
127  break;
128  case kS128:
129  assm->st_b(src.fp().toW(), dst);
130  break;
131  default:
132  UNREACHABLE();
133  }
134 }
135 
136 inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register base, int32_t offset,
137  LiftoffRegister src, ValueKind kind) {
138  MemOperand dst(base, offset);
139  Store(assm, dst, src, kind);
140 }

142 inline void push(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
143  switch (kind) {
144  case kI32:
145  assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
146  assm->sw(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
147  break;
148  case kI64:
149  case kRefNull:
150  case kRef:
151  assm->push(reg.gp());
152  break;
153  case kF32:
154  assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
155  assm->swc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
156  break;
157  case kF64:
158  assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
159  assm->Sdc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
160  break;
161  case kS128:
162  assm->daddiu(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize * 2);
163  assm->st_b(reg.fp().toW(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
164  break;
165  default:
166  UNREACHABLE();
167  }
168 }

170 #if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
171 inline void ChangeEndiannessLoad(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
172  LoadType type, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
173  bool is_float = false;
174  LiftoffRegister tmp = dst;
175  switch (type.value()) {
176  case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
177  case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
178  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
179  case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
180  // No need to change endianness for byte size.
181  return;
182  case LoadType::kF32Load:
183  is_float = true;
184  tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
185  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI32ReinterpretF32, tmp, dst);
186  [[fallthrough]];
187  case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
188  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapUnsigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
189  break;
190  case LoadType::kI32Load:
191  case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
192  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
193  break;
194  case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
195  case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
196  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
197  break;
198  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
199  case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
200  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapUnsigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
201  break;
202  case LoadType::kF64Load:
203  is_float = true;
204  tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
205  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI64ReinterpretF64, tmp, dst);
206  [[fallthrough]];
207  case LoadType::kI64Load:
208  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 8);
209  break;
210  default:
211  UNREACHABLE();
212  }
213 
214  if (is_float) {
215  switch (type.value()) {
216  case LoadType::kF32Load:
217  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF32ReinterpretI32, dst, tmp);
218  break;
219  case LoadType::kF64Load:
220  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF64ReinterpretI64, dst, tmp);
221  break;
222  default:
223  UNREACHABLE();
224  }
225  }
226 }
227 
228 inline void ChangeEndiannessStore(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister src,
229  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
230  bool is_float = false;
231  LiftoffRegister tmp = src;
232  switch (type.value()) {
233  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
234  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
235  // No need to change endianness for byte size.
236  return;
237  case StoreType::kF32Store:
238  is_float = true;
239  tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
240  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI32ReinterpretF32, tmp, src);
241  [[fallthrough]];
242  case StoreType::kI32Store:
243  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
244  break;
245  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
246  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
247  break;
248  case StoreType::kF64Store:
249  is_float = true;
250  tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
251  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprI64ReinterpretF64, tmp, src);
252  [[fallthrough]];
253  case StoreType::kI64Store:
254  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 8);
255  break;
256  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
257  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 4);
258  break;
259  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
260  assm->MacroAssembler::ByteSwapSigned(tmp.gp(), tmp.gp(), 2);
261  break;
262  default:
263  UNREACHABLE();
264  }
265 
266  if (is_float) {
267  switch (type.value()) {
268  case StoreType::kF32Store:
269  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF32ReinterpretI32, src, tmp);
270  break;
271  case StoreType::kF64Store:
272  assm->emit_type_conversion(kExprF64ReinterpretI64, src, tmp);
273  break;
274  default:
275  UNREACHABLE();
276  }
277  }
278 }
279 #endif // V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN

286 int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
287  int offset = pc_offset();
288  // When the frame size is bigger than 4KB, we need seven instructions for
289  // stack checking, so we reserve space for this case.
290  daddiu(sp, sp, 0);
291  nop();
292  nop();
293  nop();
294  nop();
295  nop();
296  nop();
297  return offset;
298 }
299 
300 void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
301 // The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
302 // `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
303 #ifdef __clang__
304  static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
305  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
306  kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
307  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
308 #endif
309 
310  // On MIPS64, we must push at least {ra} before calling the stub, otherwise
311  // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it. So just set
312  // up the frame here.
313  EnterFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
314  LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
315  WasmValue(declared_function_index));
316  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
317 }
318 
319 void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
320  int stack_param_delta) {
321  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
322  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
323 
324  // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
325  Ld(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 8));
326  Push(scratch);
327  Ld(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 0));
328  Push(scratch);
329 
330  // Shift the whole frame upwards.
331  int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
332  for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
333  Ld(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 8));
334  Sd(scratch, MemOperand(fp, (i - stack_param_delta) * 8));
335  }
336 
337  // Set the new stack and frame pointer.
338  daddiu(sp, fp, -stack_param_delta * 8);
339  Pop(ra, fp);
340 }

344 void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
345  int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
346  bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
347  // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
348  // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
349  // for them anymore.
350  int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
351  // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
352  if (feedback_vector_slot) {
353  frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
354  }
355 
356  // We can't run out of space, just pass anything big enough to not cause the
357  // assembler to try to grow the buffer.
358  constexpr int kAvailableSpace = 256;
359  MacroAssembler patching_assembler(
360  zone(), AssemblerOptions{}, CodeObjectRequired::kNo,
361  ExternalAssemblerBuffer(buffer_start_ + offset, kAvailableSpace));
362 
363  if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
364  // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
365  // done with it.
366  patching_assembler.Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_size));
367  return;
368  }
369 
370  // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
371  // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
372  // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
373  // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
374  // replace the {__ Daddu(sp, sp, -frame_size)} with a jump to OOL code that
375  // does this "extended stack check".
376  //
377  // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
378  // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
379  // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
380  // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
381  // large frame.
382  // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
383  // {pc_offset()}).
384 
385  int imm32 = pc_offset() - offset - 3 * kInstrSize;
386  patching_assembler.BranchLong(imm32);
387 
388  // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
389  // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
390  // check in the condition code.
391  RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
392  Label continuation;
393  if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
394  Register stack_limit = kScratchReg;
395  LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
396  Daddu(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
397  Branch(&continuation, uge, sp, Operand(stack_limit));
398  }
399 
400  Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
401  RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
402  // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
403  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
404  if (v8_flags.debug_code) stop();
405 
406  bind(&continuation);
407 
408  // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
409  // decrementing the SP;
410  Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_size));
411 
412  // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
413  // right after the reserved space for the {__ Daddu(sp, sp, -framesize)}
414  // (which is a Branch now).
415  int func_start_offset = offset + 7 * kInstrSize;
416  imm32 = func_start_offset - pc_offset() - 3 * kInstrSize;
417  BranchLong(imm32);
418 }

442 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
443  Label* ool_label,
444  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
445  Register budget_array = kScratchReg;
446 
447  Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
448  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
449  instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the scratch register.
450  LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
451  }
452 
453  constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
454  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
455  Ld(budget_array, MemOperand(instance_data, kArrayOffset));
456 
457  int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
458 
459  Register budget = kScratchReg2;
460  MemOperand budget_addr(budget_array, budget_arr_offset);
461  Lw(budget, budget_addr);
462  Subu(budget, budget, budget_used);
463  Sw(budget, budget_addr);
464 
465  Branch(ool_label, less, budget, Operand(zero_reg));
466 }

475 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
476  switch (value.type().kind()) {
477  case kI32:
478  MacroAssembler::li(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i32()));
479  break;
480  case kI64:
481  MacroAssembler::li(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i64()));
482  break;
483  case kF32:
484  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f32_boxed().get_bits());
485  break;
486  case kF64:
487  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits());
488  break;
489  default:
490  UNREACHABLE();
491  }
492 }

505 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
506  int offset, int size) {
507  DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
508  switch (size) {
509  case 1:
510  Lb(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
511  break;
512  case 4:
513  Lw(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
514  break;
515  case 8:
516  Ld(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
517  break;
518  default:
519  UNIMPLEMENTED();
520  }
521 }

536 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTaggedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
537  Register offset_reg,
538  int32_t offset_imm,
539  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
540  bool needs_shift) {
541  static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt64Size);
542  unsigned shift_amount = !needs_shift ? 0 : 3;
543  MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
544  false, shift_amount);
545  Ld(dst, src_op);
546 
547  // Since LoadTaggedField might start with an instruction loading an immediate
548  // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
549  // calling it.
550  if (protected_load_pc) {
551  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
552  }
553 }

556  int32_t offset_imm) {
557  static_assert(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
558  LoadTaggedPointer(dst, src_addr, no_reg, offset_imm);
559 }

566 
567 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
568  Register offset_reg,
569  int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
570  LiftoffRegList pinned,
571  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
572  SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
573  static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt64Size);
574  Register scratch = kScratchReg2;
575  MemOperand dst_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
576  Sd(src, dst_op);
577 
578  // Since StoreTaggedField might start with an instruction loading an immediate
579  // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
580  // calling it.
581  if (protected_store_pc) {
582  *protected_store_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
583  }
584 
585  if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
586 
587  Label exit;
588  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, scratch,
589  MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, kZero, &exit);
590  JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
591  CheckPageFlag(src, scratch, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
592  eq, &exit);
593  Daddu(scratch, dst_op.rm(), dst_op.offset());
594  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, scratch, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
595  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
596  bind(&exit);
597 }
598 
599 void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
600  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
601  LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
602  bool is_load_mem, bool i64_offset,
603  bool needs_shift) {
604  unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
605  MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
606  i64_offset, shift_amount);
607 
608  switch (type.value()) {
609  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
610  case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
611  Lbu(dst.gp(), src_op);
612  break;
613  case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
614  case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
615  Lb(dst.gp(), src_op);
616  break;
617  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
618  case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
619  MacroAssembler::Ulhu(dst.gp(), src_op);
620  break;
621  case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
622  case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
623  MacroAssembler::Ulh(dst.gp(), src_op);
624  break;
625  case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
626  MacroAssembler::Ulwu(dst.gp(), src_op);
627  break;
628  case LoadType::kI32Load:
629  case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
630  MacroAssembler::Ulw(dst.gp(), src_op);
631  break;
632  case LoadType::kI64Load:
633  MacroAssembler::Uld(dst.gp(), src_op);
634  break;
635  case LoadType::kF32Load:
636  MacroAssembler::Ulwc1(dst.fp(), src_op, t8);
637  break;
638  case LoadType::kF32LoadF16:
639  UNIMPLEMENTED();
640  break;
641  case LoadType::kF64Load:
642  MacroAssembler::Uldc1(dst.fp(), src_op, t8);
643  break;
644  case LoadType::kS128Load:
645  MacroAssembler::ld_b(dst.fp().toW(), src_op);
646  break;
647  default:
648  UNREACHABLE();
649  }
650 
651 #if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
652  if (is_load_mem) {
653  pinned.set(src_op.rm());
654  liftoff::ChangeEndiannessLoad(this, dst, type, pinned);
655  }
656 #endif
657  // Since load macros might start with an instruction loading an immediate
658  // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
659  // calling them.
660  if (protected_load_pc) {
661  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
662  }
663 }
664 
665 void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
666  uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
667  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
668  uint32_t* protected_store_pc, bool is_store_mem,
669  bool i64_offset) {
670  MemOperand dst_op =
671  liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
672 
673 #if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
674  if (is_store_mem) {
675  pinned.set(dst_op.rm());
676  LiftoffRegister tmp = kScratchReg2;
677  // Save original value.
678  Move(tmp, src, type.value_type());
679 
680  src = tmp;
681  pinned.set(tmp);
682  liftoff::ChangeEndiannessStore(this, src, type, pinned);
683  }
684 #endif
685 
686  switch (type.value()) {
687  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
688  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
689  Sb(src.gp(), dst_op);
690  break;
691  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
692  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
693  MacroAssembler::Ush(src.gp(), dst_op, t8);
694  break;
695  case StoreType::kI32Store:
696  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
697  MacroAssembler::Usw(src.gp(), dst_op);
698  break;
699  case StoreType::kI64Store:
700  MacroAssembler::Usd(src.gp(), dst_op);
701  break;
702  case StoreType::kF32Store:
703  MacroAssembler::Uswc1(src.fp(), dst_op, t8);
704  break;
705  case StoreType::kF32StoreF16:
706  UNIMPLEMENTED();
707  break;
708  case StoreType::kF64Store:
709  MacroAssembler::Usdc1(src.fp(), dst_op, t8);
710  break;
711  case StoreType::kS128Store:
712  MacroAssembler::st_b(src.fp().toW(), dst_op);
713  break;
714  default:
715  UNREACHABLE();
716  }
717 
718  // Since store macros might start with an instruction loading an immediate
719  // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_store_pc} after
720  // calling them.
721  if (protected_store_pc) {
722  *protected_store_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
723  }
724 }

726 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
727  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
728  LoadType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
729  bool i64_offset) {
730  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
731  MemOperand src_op =
732  liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
733  switch (type.value()) {
734  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
735  case LoadType::kI64Load8U: {
736  Lbu(dst.gp(), src_op);
737  sync();
738  return;
739  }
740  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
741  case LoadType::kI64Load16U: {
742  Lhu(dst.gp(), src_op);
743  sync();
744  return;
745  }
746  case LoadType::kI32Load: {
747  Lw(dst.gp(), src_op);
748  sync();
749  return;
750  }
751  case LoadType::kI64Load32U: {
752  Lwu(dst.gp(), src_op);
753  sync();
754  return;
755  }
756  case LoadType::kI64Load: {
757  Ld(dst.gp(), src_op);
758  sync();
759  return;
760  }
761  default:
762  UNREACHABLE();
763  }
764 }

766 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoadTaggedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
767  Register offset_reg,
768  int32_t offset_imm,
769  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order,
770  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
771  bool needs_shift) {
772  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
773  MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
774  uint32_t pc_offset_of_load = 0;
775 
776 #if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
777  UNIMPLEMENTED();
778 #else
779  Ld(dst, src_op);
780  pc_offset_of_load = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
781  sync();
782 #endif
783  if (protected_load_pc != nullptr) {
784  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset_of_load;
785  }
786 }

832 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(load_linked, store_conditional, bin_instr) \
833  do { \
834  Label binop; \
835  sync(); \
836  bind(&binop); \
837  load_linked(result.gp(), MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
838  bin_instr(temp1, result.gp(), Operand(value.gp())); \
839  store_conditional(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
840  BranchShort(&binop, eq, temp1, Operand(zero_reg)); \

981 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(
982  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
983  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
984  // Perform the atomic exchange.
985  {
986  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result};
987  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
988  Register temp0 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
989  Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
990  MemOperand dst_op =
991  liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, false);
992  Daddu(temp0, dst_op.rm(), dst_op.offset());
993  if constexpr (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
994  UNREACHABLE();
995  } else {
996  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Lld, Scd);
997  }
998  }
999 
1000  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
1001  // Emit the write barrier.
1002  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1003  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1004  Label exit;
1005  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, scratch,
1006  MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, kZero, &exit);
1007  JumpIfSmi(value.gp(), &exit);
1008  CheckPageFlag(value.gp(), scratch,
1009  MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
1010 
1011  if (offset_reg.is_valid()) {
1012  Dext(scratch, offset_reg, 0, 32);
1013  } else {
1014  li(scratch, offset_imm);
1015  }
1016  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, scratch, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
1017  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
1018  bind(&exit);
1019 }
1020 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER
1021 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT
1022 
1023 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(load_linked, \
1024  store_conditional) \
1025  do { \
1026  Label compareExchange; \
1027  Label exit; \
1028  sync(); \
1029  bind(&compareExchange); \
1030  load_linked(result.gp(), MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
1031  BranchShort(&exit, ne, expected.gp(), Operand(result.gp())); \
1032  mov(temp2, new_value.gp()); \
1033  store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
1034  BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
1035  bind(&exit); \
1036  sync(); \
1037  } while (0)
1038 
1039 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT( \
1040  load_linked, store_conditional, size, aligned) \
1041  do { \
1042  Label compareExchange; \
1043  Label exit; \
1044  andi(temp1, temp0, aligned); \
1045  Dsubu(temp0, temp0, Operand(temp1)); \
1046  sll(temp1, temp1, 3); \
1047  sync(); \
1048  bind(&compareExchange); \
1049  load_linked(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
1050  ExtractBits(result.gp(), temp2, temp1, size, false); \
1051  ExtractBits(temp2, expected.gp(), zero_reg, size, false); \
1052  BranchShort(&exit, ne, temp2, Operand(result.gp())); \
1053  InsertBits(temp2, new_value.gp(), temp1, size); \
1054  store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
1055  BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
1056  bind(&exit); \
1057  sync(); \
1058  } while (0)

1123 void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1124  ValueKind kind) {
1125  DCHECK_NE(dst_offset, src_offset);
1126  Register scratch = kScratchReg;
1127 
1128  switch (kind) {
1129  case kI32:
1130  case kF32:

1134  case kI64:

1142  default:
1143  UNREACHABLE();
1144  }

1163 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1164  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1165  MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1166  switch (kind) {
1167  case kI32:
1168  Sw(reg.gp(), dst);
1169  break;
1170  case kI64:
1171  case kRef:
1172  case kRefNull:
1173  Sd(reg.gp(), dst);
1174  break;
1175  case kF32:
1176  Swc1(reg.fp(), dst);
1177  break;
1178  case kF64:
1179  MacroAssembler::Sdc1(reg.fp(), dst);
1180  break;
1181  case kS128:
1182  MacroAssembler::st_b(reg.fp().toW(), dst);
1183  break;
1184  default:
1185  UNREACHABLE();
1186  }
1187 }

1189 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1190  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1191  MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1192  switch (value.type().kind()) {
1193  case kI32: {
1194  MacroAssembler::li(kScratchReg, Operand(value.to_i32()));
1195  Sw(kScratchReg, dst);
1196  break;
1197  }
1198  case kI64:
1199  case kRef:
1200  case kRefNull: {
1201  MacroAssembler::li(kScratchReg, value.to_i64());
1202  Sd(kScratchReg, dst);
1203  break;
1204  }
1205  default:
1206  // kWasmF32 and kWasmF64 are unreachable, since those
1207  // constants are not tracked.
1208  UNREACHABLE();
1209  }
1210 }
1211 
1212 void LiftoffAssembler::Fill(LiftoffRegister reg, int offset, ValueKind kind) {
1213  MemOperand src = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1214  switch (kind) {
1215  case kI32:
1216  Lw(reg.gp(), src);
1217  break;
1218  case kI64:
1219  case kRef:
1220  case kRefNull:
1221  Ld(reg.gp(), src);
1222  break;
1223  case kF32:
1224  Lwc1(reg.fp(), src);
1225  break;
1226  case kF64:
1227  MacroAssembler::Ldc1(reg.fp(), src);
1228  break;
1229  case kS128:
1230  MacroAssembler::ld_b(reg.fp().toW(), src);
1231  break;
1232  default:
1233  UNREACHABLE();
1234  }
1235 }

1238  UNREACHABLE();
1239 }
1240 
1241 void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1242  DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1243  RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1244 
1245  if (size <= 12 * kStackSlotSize) {
1246  // Special straight-line code for up to 12 slots. Generates one
1247  // instruction per slot (<= 12 instructions total).
1248  uint32_t remainder = size;
1249  for (; remainder >= kStackSlotSize; remainder -= kStackSlotSize) {
1250  Sd(zero_reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1251  }
1252  DCHECK(remainder == 4 || remainder == 0);
1253  if (remainder) {
1254  Sw(zero_reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1255  }
1256  } else {
1257  // General case for bigger counts (12 instructions).
1258  // Use a0 for start address (inclusive), a1 for end address (exclusive).
1259  Push(a1, a0);
1260  Daddu(a0, fp, Operand(-start - size));
1261  Daddu(a1, fp, Operand(-start));
1262 
1263  Label loop;
1264  bind(&loop);
1265  Sd(zero_reg, MemOperand(a0));
1266  daddiu(a0, a0, kSystemPointerSize);
1267  BranchShort(&loop, ne, a0, Operand(a1));
1268 
1269  Pop(a1, a0);
1270  }
1271 }

1292 void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
1293  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1294  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1295  SmiUntag(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1296  Daddu(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
1297  SmiTag(scratch);
1298  Sd(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));

1560 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
1561  DoubleRegister rhs) {
1562  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1563  DoubleRegister scratch = rhs;
1564  if (dst == rhs) {
1565  scratch = kScratchDoubleReg;
1566  Move_d(scratch, rhs);
1567  }
1568  if (dst != lhs) {
1569  Move_d(dst, lhs);
1570  }
1571  binsli_w(dst.toW(), scratch.toW(), 0);
1572  } else {
1573  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1574  Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
1575  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
1576  mfc1(scratch1, lhs);
1577  mfc1(scratch2, rhs);
1578  srl(scratch2, scratch2, 31);
1579  Ins(scratch1, scratch2, 31, 1);
1580  mtc1(scratch1, dst);
1581  }
1582 }

1670 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
1671  LiftoffRegister dst,
1672  LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
1673  switch (opcode) {
1674  case kExprI32ConvertI64:
1675  MacroAssembler::Ext(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0, 32);
1676  return true;
1677  case kExprI32SConvertF32: {
1678  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
1679 
1680  // Real conversion.
1681  MacroAssembler::Trunc_s_s(rounded, src.fp());
1682  trunc_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg2, rounded);
1683  mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1684  // Avoid INT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT32_MIN instead,
1685  // because INT32_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1686  MacroAssembler::Addu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1687  MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1688  MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1689 
1690  // Checking if trap.
1691  mtc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1692  cvt_s_w(kScratchDoubleReg2, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1693  MacroAssembler::CompareF32(EQ, rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1694  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1695  return true;
1696  }
1697  case kExprI32UConvertF32: {
1698  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
1699 
1700  // Real conversion.
1701  MacroAssembler::Trunc_s_s(rounded, src.fp());
1702  MacroAssembler::Trunc_uw_s(dst.gp(), rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1703  // Avoid UINT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use 0 instead,
1704  // because 0 allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1705  MacroAssembler::Addu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1706  MacroAssembler::Movz(dst.gp(), zero_reg, kScratchReg);
1707 
1708  // Checking if trap.
1709  MacroAssembler::Cvt_d_uw(kScratchDoubleReg2, dst.gp());
1710  cvt_s_d(kScratchDoubleReg2, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1711  MacroAssembler::CompareF32(EQ, rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1712  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1713  return true;
1714  }
1715  case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
1716  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
1717 
1718  // Real conversion.
1719  MacroAssembler::Trunc_d_d(rounded, src.fp());
1720  trunc_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg2, rounded);
1721  mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1722 
1723  // Checking if trap.
1724  cvt_d_w(kScratchDoubleReg2, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1725  MacroAssembler::CompareF64(EQ, rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1726  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1727  return true;
1728  }
1729  case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
1730  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
1731 
1732  // Real conversion.
1733  MacroAssembler::Trunc_d_d(rounded, src.fp());
1734  MacroAssembler::Trunc_uw_d(dst.gp(), rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1735 
1736  // Checking if trap.
1737  MacroAssembler::Cvt_d_uw(kScratchDoubleReg2, dst.gp());
1738  MacroAssembler::CompareF64(EQ, rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1739  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1740  return true;
1741  }
1742  case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
1743  MacroAssembler::FmoveLow(dst.gp(), src.fp());
1744  return true;
1745  case kExprI64SConvertI32:
1746  sll(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0);
1747  return true;
1748  case kExprI64UConvertI32:
1749  MacroAssembler::Dext(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0, 32);
1750  return true;
1751  case kExprI64SConvertF32: {
1752  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
1753 
1754  // Real conversion.
1755  MacroAssembler::Trunc_s_s(rounded, src.fp());
1756  trunc_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg2, rounded);
1757  dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1758  // Avoid INT64_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT64_MIN instead,
1759  // because INT64_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1760  MacroAssembler::Daddu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1761  MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1762  MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1763 
1764  // Checking if trap.
1765  dmtc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1766  cvt_s_l(kScratchDoubleReg2, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1767  MacroAssembler::CompareF32(EQ, rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1768  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1769  return true;
1770  }
1771  case kExprI64UConvertF32: {
1772  // Real conversion.
1773  MacroAssembler::Trunc_ul_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg,
1774  kScratchReg);
1775 
1776  // Checking if trap.
1777  MacroAssembler::Branch(trap, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
1778  return true;
1779  }
1780  case kExprI64SConvertF64: {
1781  DoubleRegister rounded = kScratchDoubleReg;
1782 
1783  // Real conversion.
1784  MacroAssembler::Trunc_d_d(rounded, src.fp());
1785  trunc_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg2, rounded);
1786  dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1787  // Avoid INT64_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT64_MIN instead,
1788  // because INT64_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1789  MacroAssembler::Daddu(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1790  MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1791  MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1792 
1793  // Checking if trap.
1794  dmtc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg2);
1795  cvt_d_l(kScratchDoubleReg2, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1796  MacroAssembler::CompareF64(EQ, rounded, kScratchDoubleReg2);
1797  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1798  return true;
1799  }
1800  case kExprI64UConvertF64: {
1801  // Real conversion.
1802  MacroAssembler::Trunc_ul_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg,
1803  kScratchReg);
1804 
1805  // Checking if trap.
1806  MacroAssembler::Branch(trap, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
1807  return true;
1808  }
1809  case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
1810  dmfc1(dst.gp(), src.fp());
1811  return true;
1812  case kExprF32SConvertI32: {
1813  LiftoffRegister scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
1814  mtc1(src.gp(), scratch.fp());
1815  cvt_s_w(dst.fp(), scratch.fp());
1816  return true;
1817  }
1818  case kExprF32UConvertI32:
1819  MacroAssembler::Cvt_s_uw(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1820  return true;
1821  case kExprF32ConvertF64:
1822  cvt_s_d(dst.fp(), src.fp());
1823  return true;
1824  case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
1825  MacroAssembler::FmoveLow(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1826  return true;
1827  case kExprF64SConvertI32: {
1828  LiftoffRegister scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
1829  mtc1(src.gp(), scratch.fp());
1830  cvt_d_w(dst.fp(), scratch.fp());
1831  return true;
1832  }
1833  case kExprF64UConvertI32:
1834  MacroAssembler::Cvt_d_uw(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1835  return true;
1836  case kExprF64ConvertF32:
1837  cvt_d_s(dst.fp(), src.fp());
1838  return true;
1839  case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
1840  dmtc1(src.gp(), dst.fp());
1841  return true;
1842  case kExprI32SConvertSatF32: {
1843  // Other arches use round to zero here, so we follow.
1844  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1845  trunc_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1846  mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1847  } else {
1848  Label done;
1849  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1850  CompareIsNanF32(src.fp(), src.fp());
1851  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1852  li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int32_t>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1853  MacroAssembler::Move(
1854  kScratchDoubleReg,
1855  static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1856  CompareF32(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1857  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1858  trunc_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1859  mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1860  bind(&done);
1861  }
1862  return true;
1863  }
1864  case kExprI32UConvertSatF32: {
1865  Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1866  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1867  MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<float>(0.0));
1868  CompareF32(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1869  BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1870  Trunc_uw_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1871  bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1872  return true;
1873  }
1874  case kExprI32SConvertSatF64: {
1875  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1876  trunc_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1877  mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1878  } else {
1879  Label done;
1880  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1881  CompareIsNanF64(src.fp(), src.fp());
1882  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1883  li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int32_t>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1884  MacroAssembler::Move(
1885  kScratchDoubleReg,
1886  static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()));
1887  CompareF64(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1888  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1889  trunc_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1890  mfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1891  bind(&done);
1892  }
1893  return true;
1894  }
1895  case kExprI32UConvertSatF64: {
1896  Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1897  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1898  MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<double>(0.0));
1899  CompareF64(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1900  BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1901  Trunc_uw_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1902  bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1903  return true;
1904  }
1905  case kExprI64SConvertSatF32: {
1906  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1907  trunc_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1908  dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1909  } else {
1910  Label done;
1911  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1912  CompareIsNanF32(src.fp(), src.fp());
1913  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1914  li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1915  MacroAssembler::Move(
1916  kScratchDoubleReg,
1917  static_cast<float>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1918  CompareF32(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1919  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1920  trunc_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1921  dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1922  bind(&done);
1923  }
1924  return true;
1925  }
1926  case kExprI64UConvertSatF32: {
1927  Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1928  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1929  MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<float>(0.0));
1930  CompareF32(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1931  BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1932  Trunc_ul_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, no_reg);
1933  bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1934  return true;
1935  }
1936  case kExprI64SConvertSatF64: {
1937  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MIPS_SIMD)) {
1938  trunc_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1939  dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1940  } else {
1941  Label done;
1942  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1943  CompareIsNanF64(src.fp(), src.fp());
1944  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1945  li(dst.gp(), static_cast<int64_t>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1946  MacroAssembler::Move(
1947  kScratchDoubleReg,
1948  static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
1949  CompareF64(OLT, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1950  BranchTrueShortF(&done);
1951  trunc_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1952  dmfc1(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1953  bind(&done);
1954  }
1955  return true;
1956  }
1957  case kExprI64UConvertSatF64: {
1958  Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1959  mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1960  MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<double>(0.0));
1961  CompareF64(ULE, src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1962  BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1963  Trunc_ul_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, no_reg);
1964  bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1965  return true;
1966  }
1967  default:
1968  return false;
1969  }
1970 }

2005  Register rhs,
2006  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {

2012  (is_reference(kind) && (cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual)));
2013  MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(rhs));
2014  }

2050 inline FPUCondition ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(Condition condition,
2051  bool* predicate) {
2052  switch (condition) {
2053  case kEqual:
2054  *predicate = true;
2055  return EQ;
2056  case kNotEqual:
2057  *predicate = false;
2058  return EQ;
2059  case kUnsignedLessThan:
2060  *predicate = true;
2061  return OLT;
2062  case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
2063  *predicate = false;
2064  return OLT;
2065  case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
2066  *predicate = true;
2067  return OLE;
2068  case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
2069  *predicate = false;
2070  return OLE;
2071  default:
2072  *predicate = true;
2073  break;
2074  }
2075  UNREACHABLE();
2076 }

2078 inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2079  LiftoffRegister src) {
2080  Label all_false;
2081  assm->BranchMSA(&all_false, MSA_BRANCH_V, all_zero, src.fp().toW(),
2082  USE_DELAY_SLOT);
2083  assm->li(dst.gp(), 0l);
2084  assm->li(dst.gp(), 1);
2085  assm->bind(&all_false);
2086 }
2087 
2088 inline void EmitAllTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2089  LiftoffRegister src, MSABranchDF msa_branch_df) {
2090  Label all_true;
2091  assm->BranchMSA(&all_true, msa_branch_df, all_not_zero, src.fp().toW(),
2092  USE_DELAY_SLOT);
2093  assm->li(dst.gp(), 1);
2094  assm->li(dst.gp(), 0l);
2095  assm->bind(&all_true);
2096 }

2098 inline void StoreToMemory(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst,
2099  const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
2100  if (src.is_reg()) {
2101  Store(assm, dst, src.reg(), src.kind());
2102  return;
2103  }
2104 
2105  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
2106  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
2107  if (src.is_const()) {
2108  if (src.i32_const() == 0) {
2109  temp = zero_reg;
2110  } else {
2111  assm->li(temp, src.i32_const());
2112  }
2113  } else {
2114  DCHECK(src.is_stack());
2115  if (value_kind_size(src.kind()) == 4) {
2116  assm->Lw(temp, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
2117  } else {
2118  assm->Ld(temp, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
2119  }
2120  }
2121 
2122  if (value_kind_size(src.kind()) == 4) {
2123  assm->Sw(temp, dst);
2124  } else {
2125  DCHECK_EQ(8, value_kind_size(src.kind()));
2126  assm->Sd(temp, dst);
2127  }
2128 }

2132 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2133  DoubleRegister lhs,
2134  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2135  Label not_nan, cont;
2136  MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF32(lhs, rhs);
2137  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(&not_nan);
2138  // If one of the operands is NaN, return 1 for f32.ne, else 0.
2139  if (cond == ne) {
2140  MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2141  } else {
2142  MacroAssembler::Move(dst, zero_reg);
2143  }
2144  MacroAssembler::Branch(&cont);
2145 
2146  bind(&not_nan);
2147 
2148  MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2149  bool predicate;
2150  FPUCondition fcond = liftoff::ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(cond, &predicate);
2151  MacroAssembler::CompareF32(fcond, lhs, rhs);
2152  if (predicate) {
2153  MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfNotFPUCondition(dst);
2154  } else {
2155  MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfFPUCondition(dst);
2156  }
2157 
2158  bind(&cont);
2159 }

2163  DoubleRegister rhs) {

2166  MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(&not_nan);

2168  if (cond == ne) {
2169  MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
2170  } else {
2171  MacroAssembler::Move(dst, zero_reg);
2172  }

2174

2178  bool predicate;
2179  FPUCondition fcond = liftoff::ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(cond, &predicate);
2180  MacroAssembler::CompareF64(fcond, lhs, rhs);

2182  MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfNotFPUCondition(dst);

2197 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_smi_check(Register obj, Label* target,
2198  SmiCheckMode mode,
2199  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2200  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2201  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2202  And(scratch, obj, Operand(kSmiTagMask));
2203  Condition condition = mode == kJumpOnSmi ? eq : ne;
2204  Branch(target, condition, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
2205 }

2207 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2208  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2209  LoadType type,
2210  LoadTransformationKind transform,
2211  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2212  bool i64_offset) {
2213  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2214  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2215  MemOperand src_op =
2216  liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
2217  MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2218  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2219  MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2220 
2221  if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2222  Ld(scratch, src_op);
2223  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2224  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2225  clti_s_b(kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa, 0);
2226  ilvr_b(dst_msa, kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa);
2227  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2228  xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2229  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2230  ilvr_b(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, dst_msa);
2231  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2232  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2233  clti_s_h(kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa, 0);
2234  ilvr_h(dst_msa, kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa);
2235  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2236  xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2237  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2238  ilvr_h(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, dst_msa);
2239  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2240  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2241  clti_s_w(kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa, 0);
2242  ilvr_w(dst_msa, kSimd128ScratchReg, dst_msa);
2243  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2244  xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2245  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2246  ilvr_w(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, dst_msa);
2247  }
2248  } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2249  xor_v(dst_msa, dst_msa, dst_msa);
2250  if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2251  Lwu(scratch, src_op);
2252  insert_w(dst_msa, 0, scratch);
2253  } else {
2254  DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2255  Ld(scratch, src_op);
2256  insert_d(dst_msa, 0, scratch);
2257  }
2258  } else {
2259  DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2260  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2261  Lb(scratch, src_op);
2262  fill_b(dst_msa, scratch);
2263  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2264  Lh(scratch, src_op);
2265  fill_h(dst_msa, scratch);
2266  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2267  Lw(scratch, src_op);
2268  fill_w(dst_msa, scratch);
2269  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2270  Ld(scratch, src_op);
2271  fill_d(dst_msa, scratch);
2272  }
2273  }
2274 }

2276 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2277  Register addr, Register offset_reg,
2278  uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
2279  uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2280  bool i64_offset) {
2281  MemOperand src_op =
2282  liftoff::GetMemOp(this, addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
2283  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2284  LoadStoreLaneParams load_params(type.mem_type().representation(), laneidx);
2285  MacroAssembler::LoadLane(load_params.sz, dst.fp().toW(), laneidx, src_op);
2286 }

2288 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,

2290  StoreType type, uint8_t lane,

2300 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
2301  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2302  LiftoffRegister rhs,
2303  const uint8_t shuffle[16],
2304  bool is_swizzle) {
2305  MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2306  MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
2307  MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
2308 
2309  uint64_t control_hi = 0;
2310  uint64_t control_low = 0;
2311  for (int i = 7; i >= 0; i--) {
2312  control_hi <<= 8;
2313  control_hi |= shuffle[i + 8];
2314  control_low <<= 8;
2315  control_low |= shuffle[i];
2316  }
2317 
2318  if (dst_msa == lhs_msa) {
2319  move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, lhs_msa);
2320  lhs_msa = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2321  } else if (dst_msa == rhs_msa) {
2322  move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, rhs_msa);
2323  rhs_msa = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2324  }
2325 
2326  li(kScratchReg, control_low);
2327  insert_d(dst_msa, 0, kScratchReg);
2328  li(kScratchReg, control_hi);
2329  insert_d(dst_msa, 1, kScratchReg);
2330  vshf_b(dst_msa, rhs_msa, lhs_msa);
2331 }
2332 
2333 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_swizzle(LiftoffRegister dst,
2334  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2335  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2336  MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
2337  MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
2338  MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
2339 
2340  if (dst == lhs) {
2341  move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, lhs_msa);
2342  lhs_msa = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2343  }
2344  xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
2345  move_v(dst_msa, rhs_msa);
2346  vshf_b(dst_msa, kSimd128RegZero, lhs_msa);
2347 }

3172 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_min(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3173  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3174  MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
3175  MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
3176  MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
3177  MSARegister scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
3178  MSARegister scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
3179  // If inputs are -0.0. and +0.0, then write -0.0 to scratch1.
3180  // scratch1 = (lhs == rhs) ? (lhs | rhs) : (rhs | rhs).
3181  fseq_w(scratch0, lhs_msa, rhs_msa);
3182  bsel_v(scratch0, rhs_msa, lhs_msa);
3183  or_v(scratch1, scratch0, rhs_msa);
3184  // scratch0 = isNaN(scratch1) ? scratch1: lhs.
3185  fseq_w(scratch0, scratch1, scratch1);
3186  bsel_v(scratch0, scratch1, lhs_msa);
3187  // dst = (scratch1 <= scratch0) ? scratch1 : scratch0.
3188  fsle_w(dst_msa, scratch1, scratch0);
3189  bsel_v(dst_msa, scratch0, scratch1);
3190  // Canonicalize the result.
3191  fmin_w(dst_msa, dst_msa, dst_msa);
3192 }
3193 
3194 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_max(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3195  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3196  MSARegister dst_msa = dst.fp().toW();
3197  MSARegister lhs_msa = lhs.fp().toW();
3198  MSARegister rhs_msa = rhs.fp().toW();
3199  MSARegister scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
3200  MSARegister scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
3201  // If inputs are -0.0. and +0.0, then write +0.0 to scratch1.
3202  // scratch1 = (lhs == rhs) ? (lhs | rhs) : (rhs | rhs).
3203  fseq_w(scratch0, lhs_msa, rhs_msa);
3204  bsel_v(scratch0, rhs_msa, lhs_msa);
3205  and_v(scratch1, scratch0, rhs_msa);
3206  // scratch0 = isNaN(scratch1) ? scratch1: lhs.
3207  fseq_w(scratch0, scratch1, scratch1);
3208  bsel_v(scratch0, scratch1, lhs_msa);
3209  // dst = (scratch0 <= scratch1) ? scratch1 : scratch0.
3210  fsle_w(dst_msa, scratch0, scratch1);
3211  bsel_v(dst_msa, scratch0, scratch1);
3212  // Canonicalize the result.
3213  fmax_w(dst_msa, dst_msa, dst_msa);
3214 }

3896 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_inc_i32_at(Address address) {
3897  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3898  Register counter_addr = temps.Acquire();
3899  Register value = temps.Acquire();
3900  li(counter_addr, Operand(static_cast<uint64_t>(address)));
3901  Lw(value, MemOperand(counter_addr, 0));
3902  Daddu(value, value, Operand(1));
3903  Sw(value, MemOperand(counter_addr, 0));
3904 }

3916 void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
3917  LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
3918  unsigned num_gp_regs = gp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
3919  if (num_gp_regs) {
3920  unsigned offset = num_gp_regs * kSystemPointerSize;
3921  daddiu(sp, sp, -offset);
3922  while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
3923  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3924  offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
3925  sd(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3926  gp_regs.clear(reg);
3927  }
3928  DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
3929  }
3930  LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
3931  unsigned num_fp_regs = fp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
3932  if (num_fp_regs) {
3933  unsigned slot_size = IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD) ? 16 : 8;
3934  daddiu(sp, sp, -(num_fp_regs * slot_size));
3935  unsigned offset = 0;
3936  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
3937  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3938  if (IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD)) {
3939  MacroAssembler::st_d(reg.fp().toW(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3940  } else {
3941  MacroAssembler::Sdc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3942  }
3943  fp_regs.clear(reg);
3944  offset += slot_size;
3945  }
3946  DCHECK_EQ(offset, num_fp_regs * slot_size);
3947  }
3948 }
3949 
3950 void LiftoffAssembler::PopRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
3951  LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
3952  unsigned fp_offset = 0;
3953  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
3954  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3955  if (IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD)) {
3956  MacroAssembler::ld_d(reg.fp().toW(), MemOperand(sp, fp_offset));
3957  } else {
3958  MacroAssembler::Ldc1(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, fp_offset));
3959  }
3960  fp_regs.clear(reg);
3961  fp_offset += (IsEnabled(MIPS_SIMD) ? 16 : 8);
3962  }
3963  if (fp_offset) daddiu(sp, sp, fp_offset);
3964  LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
3965  unsigned gp_offset = 0;
3966  while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
3967  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
3968  ld(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, gp_offset));
3969  gp_regs.clear(reg);
3970  gp_offset += kSystemPointerSize;
3971  }
3972  daddiu(sp, sp, gp_offset);
3973 }
3974 
3975 void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
3976  SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
3977  LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
3978  LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
3979  int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
3980  LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
3981  while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
3982  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetFirstRegSet();
3983  if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
3984  safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
3985  }
3986  gp_spills.clear(reg);
3987  ++spill_offset;
3988  spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
3989  }
3990  // Record the number of additional spill slots.
3991  RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
3992 }

3994 void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
3995  DCHECK_LT(num_stack_slots,
3996  (1 << 16) / kSystemPointerSize); // 16 bit immediate
3997  MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(static_cast<int>(num_stack_slots));
3998 }

4000 void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
4001  const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
4002  ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
4003  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4004  Daddu(sp, sp, -stack_bytes);
4005 
4006  int arg_offset = 0;
4007  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
4008  liftoff::StoreToMemory(this, MemOperand{sp, arg_offset}, arg);
4009  arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
4010  }
4011  DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
4012 
4013  // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function.
4014  // On mips, the first argument is passed in {a0}.
4015  constexpr Register kFirstArgReg = a0;
4016  mov(kFirstArgReg, sp);
4017 
4018  // Now call the C function.
4019  constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
4020  PrepareCallCFunction(kNumCCallArgs, kScratchReg);
4021  CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
4022 
4023  // Move return value to the right register.
4024  const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
4025  if (return_kind != kVoid) {
4026  constexpr Register kReturnReg = v0;
4027 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
4028  // When calling a host function in the simulator, if the function returns an
4029  // int32 value, the simulator does not sign-extend it to int64 because in
4030  // the simulator we do not know whether the function returns an int32 or
4031  // int64. So we need to sign extend it here.
4032  if (return_kind == kI32) {
4033  sll(next_result_reg->gp(), kReturnReg, 0);
4034  } else if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
4035  Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
4036  }
4037 #else
4038  if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
4039  Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
4040  }
4041 #endif
4042  ++next_result_reg;
4043  }
4044 
4045  // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
4046  if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
4047  liftoff::Load(this, *next_result_reg, MemOperand(sp, 0), out_argument_kind);
4048  }
4049 
4050  Daddu(sp, sp, stack_bytes);
4051 }
4052 
4053 void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args_list,
4054  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4055  // First, prepare the stack for the C call.
4056  const int num_args = static_cast<int>(args_list.size());
4057  PrepareCallCFunction(num_args, kScratchReg);
4058 
4059  // Note: If we ever need more than eight arguments we would need to load the
4060  // stack arguments to registers (via LoadToRegister), then push them to the
4061  // stack.
4062 
4063  // Execute the parallel register move for register parameters.
4064  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(kCArgRegs), num_args);
4065  const VarState* const args = args_list.begin();
4066  ParallelMove parallel_move{this};
4067  for (int reg_arg = 0; reg_arg < num_args; ++reg_arg) {
4068  parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(LiftoffRegister{kCArgRegs[reg_arg]},
4069  args[reg_arg]);
4070  }
4071  parallel_move.Execute();
4072 
4073  // Now call the C function.
4074  CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_args);
4075 }

4117 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst, FPURegister src,
4118  ValueKind kind) {
4119  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4120  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4121  Label not_nan;
4122  if (kind == kF32) {
4123  CompareIsNanF32(src, src);
4124  } else {
4125  DCHECK_EQ(kind, kF64);
4126  CompareIsNanF64(src, src);
4127  }
4128  BranchFalseShortF(&not_nan, USE_DELAY_SLOT);
4129  li(scratch, 1);
4130  Sw(dst, MemOperand(dst));
4131  bind(&not_nan);
4132 }
4133 
4134 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4135  LiftoffRegister src,
4136  Register tmp_gp,
4137  LiftoffRegister tmp_s128,
4138  ValueKind lane_kind) {
4139  Label not_nan;
4140  if (lane_kind == kF32) {
4141  fcun_w(tmp_s128.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW());
4142  } else {
4143  DCHECK_EQ(lane_kind, kF64);
4144  fcun_d(tmp_s128.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW(), src.fp().toW());
4145  }
4146  BranchMSA(&not_nan, MSA_BRANCH_V, all_zero, tmp_s128.fp().toW(),
4147  USE_DELAY_SLOT);
4148  li(tmp_gp, 1);
4149  Sw(tmp_gp, MemOperand(dst));
4150  bind(&not_nan);
4151 }

4155 }
4156 
4157 void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
4158  DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
4159  SortInPushOrder();
4160  int last_stack_slot = param_slots;
4161  for (auto& slot : slots_) {
4162  const int stack_slot = slot.dst_slot_;
4163  int stack_decrement = (last_stack_slot - stack_slot) * kSystemPointerSize;
4164  DCHECK_LT(0, stack_decrement);
4165  last_stack_slot = stack_slot;
4166  const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src = slot.src_;
4167  switch (src.loc()) {
4168  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack:
4169  if (src.kind() != kS128) {
4170  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
4171  asm_->Ld(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
4172  asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4173  } else {
4174  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSimd128Size);
4175  asm_->Ld(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_ - 8));
4176  asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4177  asm_->Ld(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
4178  asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4179  }
4180  break;
4181  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister: {
4182  int pushed_bytes = SlotSizeInBytes(slot);
4183  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - pushed_bytes);
4184  liftoff::push(asm_, src.reg(), src.kind());
4185  break;
4186  }

4190  asm_->push(kScratchReg);
4191  break;
4192  }
4193  }
4194  }
